    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Manually-powered cinematic apparatuses developed in France by the Lumière brothers at the end of the 19th century, which functioned as motion picture cameras, film projectors, and developers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
